 style=\"font-size: small;\">The </span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Hackathon website on </span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">datadays.eu/hackathon</span></span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"> opens on the 28 November 2013. The site will contain all the necessary registration information, rules, datasets and templates you will need to enter one or more of the competitions.</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span>Attend </span></span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\">the Competition </span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span>Briefing</span></span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\">:</span></span></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">A free workshop </span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">for interested participants will be held on Thursday, 28 November 2013, in Sint-Laureins (near Eeklo) during the </span></span></span><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.v-ict-or.be/events/52384c9ace3fb57ddd00017e\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Manage IT congress</span></span></a></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"> organised by V-ICT-OR. Please note that attendance at the workshop is not mandatory in order to take part in any of the competitions.</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\">Remember the </span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span>Closing Dates</span></span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\">:</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">1. Professional Hackathon</span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"> – Friday 1</span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><sup><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">st</span></span></sup></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"> February, 2014</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">2. Hack for Good – Friday 18</span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><sup><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">th</span></span></sup></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"> December 2013</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">3. Citizen Hackathon – Friday 1</span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><sup><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">st</span></span></sup></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"> February, 2014</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Winners will be announced at the DataDays conference </span></span></span><span style=\"color: #66696d;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Droid Sans\', \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">in Gent on the xx February 2014.</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p lang=\"en-GB\"></p>\r\n<p lang=\"en-GB\"></p>\r\n<p lang=\"en-GB\"></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p lang=\"en-GB\">\r\n\r\n</p>','Hackathon','','inherit','open','open','','71-revision-v1','','','2013-11-21 20:20:40','2013-11-21 20:20:40','',71,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/?p=72',0,'revision','',0),(74,1,'2013-11-21 20:33:04','2013-11-21 20:33:04',' ','','','publish','open','open','','74','','','2013-11-21 20:38:51','2013-11-21 20:38:51','',0,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/?p=74',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(77,1,'2013-11-21 20:37:13','2013-11-21 20:37:13','[program]','Program','','inherit','open','open','','56-revision-v1','','','2013-11-21 20:37:13','2013-11-21 20:37:13','',56,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/?p=77',0,'revision','',0),(78,1,'2013-11-21 20:38:51','2013-11-21 20:38:51',' ','','','publish','open','open','','78','','','2013-11-21 20:38:51','2013-11-21 20:38:51','',0,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/?p=78',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(79,1,'2013-11-21 20:45:38','2013-11-21 20:45:38','Join The Open Data Pioneers, practitioners, thinkers and resaerchers from across the world to unlock and advance the power of colaboration and Open Innovation in this joint conference by the Open Knowledge Foundation (OKFN), Citadel on the Move and Linked Organisation of Local Autority ICT Societies (LOLA).\n\n\n\n[program]','Home','','inherit','open','open','','2-autosave-v1','','','2013-11-21 20:45:38','2013-11-21 20:45:38','',2,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/?p=79',0,'revision','',0),(80,1,'2013-11-21 20:46:02','2013-11-21 20:46:02','Join The Open Data Pioneers, practitioners, thinkers and resaerchers from across the world to unlock and advance the power of colaboration and Open Innovation in this joint conference by the Open Knowledge Foundation (OKFN), Citadel on the Move and Linked Organisation of Local Autority ICT Societies (LOLA).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[program]','Home','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2013-11-21 20:46:02','2013-11-21 20:46:02','',2,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/?p=80',0,'revision','',0),(81,1,'2013-11-21 20:58:12','2013-11-21 20:58:12','Data Days  – Will you Scoop EUR 5,000, EUR 10,000 or even EUR 20,000?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTo promote the exciting innovation possibilities made available through \r\nOpen Data, DataDays are launching three new Hackathon competitions! \r\nThe competitions are sponsored and supported by, CORVE, V-ICT-OR, iDROPS and OKFN Belgium.\r\nOpen Belgium Competition’s\r\nAre you a programmer or designer? A hacker through and through? \r\nIf so you can be the first to start working on what may well be Flanders most valuable data set - the VKBO, ‘the Enhanced Crossroads Bank for Enterprises’ - in which all enterprises, schools, hospitals etc. are geographically localised. Using the VKBO and Uit datasets in Vlaanderen, you can develop an application, produce mashups or create visualisations and present them to the public.\r\n\r\n1. Professional Hackathon\r\nWould you like to start your own company or launch a commercial application? If so, take part in the ‘Professional Hackathon:’ \r\nProduce a working application \r\nDraft a business plan to present the results to citizens and entrepreneurs \r\nPreferably use data from the VKBO and other datasets applied throughout Flanders as a whole. \r\nDevelop a plan detailing how you can further market the app, which may result in your nomination for Apps4EU.\r\nThe Government of Flanders’ expects that applications should be up and running with a maximum of EUR 20.000.\r\nCriteria for entry include: 1) quality of the application, 2) price for making the application permanently available for at least three years and 3) sustainability of the app. The application may be further marketed by the developer.\r\n\r\n\r\n2. Hack for Good: Lets Fight Poverty!\r\nOver 30 ideas offering solutions to specific poverty related issues were conceived during eight creative miniLABs across Flanders.  Hack For Good wants to turn these ideas into reality. We are asking digital developers, business developers, coders, programmers and hackers to pitch a plan to a panel of financiers on how to implement the ideas that they think are best. The best project will win EUR 10,000 to boost social innovation. \r\nCriteria for entry include: xxxxx\r\n\r\nOpen Europe | Open World Competition\r\n\r\nAre you a creative citizen?\r\nIf so, Good News! The Citadel on the Move project is also sponsoring a competition for amateurs.\r\n3. \r\nCitizen Hackathon\r\nPerhaps you have some great ideas but do not yet possess the technical knowledge required to develop them? The Citadel on the Move project can help.  \r\nIf you have a powerful idea, use our sample apps and datasets to create a working prototype, and you could win EUR 5,000 and be nominated to take part in the wider, prestigious Apps for Europe competition.\r\n\r\n \r\nCriteria for entry include: \r\n\r\nHow to Take Part \r\nRegister:\r\nThe Hackathon website on datadays.eu/hackathon opens on the 28 November 2013.  The site will contain all the necessary registration information, rules, datasets and templates you will need to enter one or more of the competitions.\r\nAttend the Competition Briefing: \r\nA free workshop for interested participants will be held on Thursday, 28 November 2013, in Sint-Laureins (near Eeklo) during the Manage IT congress organised by V-ICT-OR. Please note that attendance at the workshop is not mandatory in order to take part in any of the competitions.\r\nRemember the Closing Dates:\r\n1. Professional Hackathon – Friday 1st February, 2014\r\n2. Hack for Good – Friday 18th December 2013\r\n3. Citizen Hackathon – Friday 1st February, 2014\r\nWinners will be announced at the DataDays conference in Gent on the xx February 2014.','Hackathon','','inherit','open','open','','71-revision-v1','','','2013-11-21 20:58:12','2013-11-21 20:58:12','',71,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/71-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(82,1,'2013-11-21 21:00:55','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-11-21 21:00:55','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/?p=82',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(83,1,'2013-11-21 21:06:07','2013-11-21 21:06:07','','leeuwVO_G_G','','inherit','open','open','','leeuwvo_g_g','','','2013-11-21 21:06:07','2013-11-21 21:06:07','',71,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/leeuwVO_G_G.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(84,1,'2013-11-21 21:06:50','2013-11-21 21:06:50','','CITADEL LOGO-1_v1.0','','inherit','open','open','','citadel-logo-1_v1-0','','','2013-11-21 21:06:50','2013-11-21 21:06:50','',71,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/CITADEL-LOGO-1_v1.0.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(85,1,'2013-11-21 21:07:13','2013-11-21 21:07:13','','SIL_logo','','inherit','open','open','','sil_logo','','','2013-11-21 21:07:13','2013-11-21 21:07:13','',71,'http://www.ed.be/datadays/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/SIL_logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(86,1,'2013-11-21 21:08:18','2013-11-21 21:08:18','','iDrops logo 2012',''